Sales Project¶

Analyze the company's sales data for the fourth quarter acoss Australia, and State by State and help the company make data driven decisions for the coming year.

  • Determine the states that are generating the highest revenues
  • Formulate sales programs for states with lower revenues.

Data Wrangling¶

Ensure that the data is clean and that there is no missing or incorrect data. Inspect the data manually for missing/incorrect data using the functions isna(), and notna().

Chandni's Analysis

DATA MANAGEMENT

  • No data is missing from any variable so imputations is not necessary. If data was missing, I would use the mean of the variable to fill in the missing data.
  • Variables Unit and Sales are both right-skewed (positive skew) and have outliers. I want to analyze "Total Sales" so I first multipled Units and Sales together to get total sales. Looking at the value it is right-skewed and has outliers, and therefore needs to be normalized.
  • I tried normalizing using fit_transform, natural log, and squareroot transformations, and the squareroot transformation did the best job of normalizing the data. Also, binning totalsales into 25 categories creates a good ordinal variable for use.

DATA ANALYSIS

  • At face value, Seniors produced the least in total sales and Women produced the most in total sales. However, on average there was no significant differences among Group by total sales.
  • VIC produced the most total sales of any state and WA produced the least total sales.
  • Total sales spiked in the 2nd and 4th week of Oct 2020, as well as in the 2nd week in Dec 2020.
  • Total sales dipped most during the month of November.
  • There is no difference in time of sale.
  • Overall, the quarter of sales sold 115,752 units, with a total sales of 6,657,890,000.

CONCLUSION

  • The states with the highest revenues are VIC (by average sales) and NSW (by sum of sales).
  • For states with low revenue, try the following:
    • bring staff from VIC and NSW to help/train staff in low-performing states
    • add sales promotions in October and December to increase sales. These are peak months in other states and more should be done to get to this potential in low-performing states.

#normalize totalsales data by first removing highest 5% of data since that's where the outliers exist.

#Create a function for p-val evaluation 
def hypothtest(p_val,alpha=0.05): 
    if p_val > alpha: 
        print("Accept the null hypothesis")
    else: 
        print("Reject the null hypothesis")
